<subSubSection pageId="21" pageNumber="22" type="discussion">
<paragraph blockId="21.[151,1436,1098,1859]" pageId="21" pageNumber="22">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[198,330,1794,1820]" pageId="21" pageNumber="22">Discussion</emphasis>
:— 
<taxonomicName box="[367,642,1795,1820]" class="Liliopsida" family="Marantaceae" genus="Monotagma" kingdom="Plantae" order="Zingiberales" pageId="21" pageNumber="22" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="congestum">
<emphasis box="[367,642,1795,1820]" italics="true" pageId="21" pageNumber="22">Monotagma congestum</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is similar to 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Hagberg" authorityYear="1988" box="[798,924,1795,1820]" class="Liliopsida" family="Marantaceae" genus="Monotagma" kingdom="Plantae" order="Zingiberales" pageId="21" pageNumber="22" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="rudanii">
<emphasis box="[798,924,1795,1820]" italics="true" pageId="21" pageNumber="22">M. rudanii</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
and 
<taxonomicName authorityName="K. Schum. ex Loesener" authorityYear="1915" box="[982,1066,1795,1820]" class="Liliopsida" family="Marantaceae" genus="Monotagma" kingdom="Plantae" order="Zingiberales" pageId="21" pageNumber="22" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="ulei">
<emphasis box="[982,1066,1795,1820]" italics="true" pageId="21" pageNumber="22">M. ulei</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, but is distinguished by a more condensed aerial shoot system with florescences forming a dense ± ovoid head.
</paragraph>
